description:
In lichen_l2.c:510-516 (the #else path when HAVE_LICHEN_LINK is 0), received data length is checked against rx_ipv6_buf size:

if (len > sizeof(rx_ipv6_buf)) {
    LOG_WRN("Packet too large: %zu", len);
    k_mutex_unlock(&rx_mutex);
    return;
}
memcpy(rx_ipv6_buf, data, len);

Location: firmware/bridge-zephyr/subsys/lichen/lichen_l2.c:510-516

The check exists, but note that rx_ipv6_buf is sized as LICHEN_L2_MTU + IPV6_BASE_HDR_LEN = 240 bytes. The LoRa radio can return up to 255 bytes (lora_recv buffer in rx_thread is 256). The existing bounds check is correct and prevents overflow.

This finding is NOT a bug - documenting that the bounds check exists and is correct. No issue filed.
